    "背景故事": "The bright moon and clear breeze cool the mat and pillow. **To Yuen-ming** (To Yuen-ming) gathers many friends to appreciate the chrysanthemums, playing the *qin*, singing, and drinking—a scene of great delight. (**To Yuen-ming** lived in the late Eastern Jin Dynasty, a time of rampant militarism and corrupt politics; he refused to compromise his principles, refusing to 'bow for five pecks of rice', and lived a contented life in retirement despite his poverty.) The Verses state: *New tune and new mode, clear breeze and bright moon, those of like mind gather, joyful and without worry.* The Quatrain offers: *His refusal to bow is a celebrated tale, the integrity of the Master of Five Willows is profound.* / The recipient of this lot shall find all matters undertaken smooth and successful, with nothing proving disadvantageous.",
    "詳情": "Residence is of peace and safety. Travellers will arrive. All matters are favourable for aspirations. Illness will see immediate recovery. A son shall be born. Marriage is extremely compatible. Sericulture and Livestock are both profitable. Wealth is certain to be achieved as desired. Fung Shui will see both progeny and prosperity forthcoming. Lost Items will be recovered soon. Personal Fortune is of peace, safety, and no illness. Joy and celebration for all for the weather/timing. Travel will see fine scenery everywhere."
