    "吉凶": "Extreme Ill-Fortune",
    "占驗古人": "Tai-bak (Li Po) Scoops the Moon (太白撈月)",
    "籤文": "The mirage of the clam's tower in the sea has no limit to its illusion, towering ten thousand *zhang* (measures) high to reach the heavens. / It may be suddenly scattered by a frantic gale, and sometimes it re-forms into a wisp of blue smoke.",
    "背景故事": "The vapours exhaled by the giant clam in the sea form a tower so high it reaches the heavens, yet a single gust of wind can scatter it. Although it may re-form after dispersal, it floats like smoke and cannot last. This is a vision of pure illusion; though pleasing to the eye, it yields no actual result. The Verses state: *Sea-mirage and clam-tower, a false illusion, blue smoke and frantic gale, seeming to exist but without substance.* The Quatrain offers: *Superficial prosperity is both true and false, the experiences of the Wine Immortal have lasted for millennia.* / The recipient of this lot must fulfil their duty and consolidate their foundation, thereby ensuring stability and permanence so that all matters are not scattered by others. This lot contains more ill-fortune than good; be wary of petty individuals and slander.",
    "詳情": "Illness is perilous. Wealth is also empty. Aspirations shall have no conclusion. Travellers have not arrived. Pregnancy is attended by ill-fortune. Sericulture and Livestock are also unavailing. Marriage is incompatible. Fame is not yet achieved. Residence is not prosperous. Fung Shui is a false setting that cannot yield prosperity. Lost Items cannot be recovered even if forcefully sought. Accumulate good deeds to avert catastrophe for personal fortune. All matters are disagreeable in weather/timing. The conclusion will certainly be disadvantageous for travel."
