    "籤文": "A plum blossom first blooms in Lingnan, its crystal petals falling into the wine cup. / Yet a man on a donkey arrived early, his intention to carry the Prime Spring Flower away.",
    "背景故事": "The plum blossoms of Lingnan bloom the earliest. When placed in a wine cup, the wine becomes intensely fragrant. One encounters a man riding a donkey who presents this plum blossom. As the flower blooms uniquely before all others, it is naturally pleasing to the heart. The Verses state: *Lingnan plum petals, fragrant and lustrous in the wine, beware of others, leading the trend alone.* The Quatrain offers: *Hou-yin (Mang Hou-yin) was not used by the world, he dedicated himself to the landscape and travelled to Guangdong.* / The recipient of this lot shall find all matters successful if guided by a benefactor. This lot is half-auspicious, half-inauspicious. Although it contains no phrase of major impediment, it suggests that an advantage (as the man on the donkey has already plucked the flower) may be seized by another, thereby turning good fortune into misfortune. The interpretation of this lot requires careful consideration.",
    "詳情": "Residence is average. Wealth is difficult to obtain. Travellers have set out. Illness is not yet recovered. Fame is difficult to achieve. Caution is advised for marriage. Sericulture is also without worry. Livestock must be managed carefully. Pregnancy will result in a son, bringing the greatest joy. Fung Shui is average and without harm. Lost Items may be recovered upon searching. Accumulate good deeds for greater vitality in personal fortune. Both cold and heat are agreeable in weather/timing. Travel will see much support from benevolent individuals."
