    "籤文": "The autumn water and rushes are full of white dew, the moon's light fills the courtyard and bathes the steps in clarity. / A clear breeze stirs the horse's bell, its sound continuous, merging with the morning bell.",
    "背景故事": "Autumn is full of dew. The moon's light fills the steps. The wind stirs the horse's bell, its sound linking with the morning bell. This describes the scene when **Siu Ho** (Siu Ho), upon learning that **Hon Sun** (Hon Sun) had left after not being fully utilised by Emperor Go-tsu (Gaozu) of Han, pursued him beneath the moonlight at Nam Zheng. The Verses state: *Clear autumn scene, moonlight fills the steps, Siu Ho pursues the worthy man, success will come at dawn.* The Quatrain offers: *The Prince of Ch'i was disappointed and fled to another land, the famous minister recognised the talent and rescued the situation.* / The recipient of this lot shall find all matters stable; although there may be minor obstruction, the outcome will ultimately be favourable. It is wholly auspicious and without misfortune.",
    "詳情": "Fame may be hoped for. Wealth is not great. Seek divine assistance for pregnancy. Marriage is also favourable. Illness is without harm. Caution is acceptable for aspirations. Livestock and Sericulture are also without impediment. Residence is of peace and safety. Travel is without obstruction. Fung Shui is average and without impediment. Recovery of lost items may be difficult. Cultivate good deeds for greater peace and safety in personal fortune. Weather/Timing is average and satisfactory. Travel is neither beneficial nor harmful."
