    "背景故事": "During the Han Dynasty, **Sou Mo** (Sou Mo) was held captive by the **Huns** (Hung-no) and was compelled to herd sheep at Lake Baikal for nineteen years, only returning home when he was a man of sixty, a moment akin to the wild goose carrying tidings across the vast river. The Verses state: *Sou Mo's faithfulness, the wild goose carries the news; though hardship is endured, the journey ends.* The Quatrain offers: *The lone sojourner has a profound purpose; the long-time prisoner shall eventually be pardoned.* / The recipient of this lot must be forbearing in all matters. All undertakings shall be smooth and successful after much effort and patience. The lot is fully auspicious and stable.",
